casebody.data:
CARLSON, Respondent, v. WINTERSEN, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 8, 1893.) Action by Louise Carlson against Marie F. Wintersen;

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, J.T.

E. F. Bullard, for appellant. H. M. Hitchings, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion for a reargument denied, with $10 costs. See 20 N. Y. Supp. 897.
